# 🌍 Natural Disaster Prediction and Management System

An open-source project focused on the prediction, analysis, and management of natural disasters using data science, machine learning, and geospatial intelligence.

## 🔍 Overview

This project aims to help predict natural disasters (such as earthquakes, floods, wildfires, and hurricanes) and assist in disaster management through timely alerts, risk assessment, and resource optimization.

## 🧠 Features

- 🌊 **Disaster Prediction Models**: ML models trained to forecast floods, earthquakes, wildfires, etc.
- 🗺️ **Geospatial Visualization**: Interactive maps and dashboards using satellite or sensor data.
- 🛰️ **Remote Sensing Integration**: Uses publicly available datasets like NASA, NOAA, and ESA.
- 🔔 **Early Warning System**: Real-time notifications and alert mechanism.
- 📈 **Risk Assessment**: Tools for estimating the potential impact of a disaster.
- 👥 **Resource Management**: Suggestions for optimizing emergency response and relief.

## 📦 Tech Stack

- **Languages**: Python, JavaScript
- **Libraries/Frameworks**: TensorFlow / PyTorch, Scikit-learn, XGBoost, Pandas, NumPy, Folium, Leaflet, Flask/Django, Streamlit
- **Visualization**: Plotly, Dash, Power BI, or GIS tools
- **Data Sources**:
  - [NASA Earth Data](https://earthdata.nasa.gov/)
  - [USGS Earthquake Data](https://earthquake.usgs.gov/)
  - [NOAA Climate Data](https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/)
  - [Copernicus Open Access Hub](https://scihub.copernicus.eu/)

